    • Constructor Detail

      • OntAggregatedObservation

        public OntAggregatedObservation(java.lang.String providerService,
                                org.apache.jena.rdf.model.RDFNode stateValue,
                                java.lang.String quantity,
                                java.lang.String activityTime,
                                java.lang.String variance,
                                java.lang.String standardDeviation,
                                java.lang.String mean,
                                java.lang.String timeWeighting)
        Method creates an aggregated ontology observation. It contains aggregated values of state changes from an unit for each providerService in a specific time frame (/period). Dependent on the kind of state value (discrete/continuous) some of the parameter are null. The parameter itself based on the data type string, because read/write from/to the ontology (SPARQL).
        Parameters:
        providerService - is the providerService to identify the kind of state values.
        stateValue - is the state value (discrete or continuous) of an state change to a specific time.
        quantity - is a statistical value to describe the quantity of fulfilled state changes.
        activityTime - is a statistical value to describe the duration of the state value in milliseconds.
        variance - is a statistical value to describe the variance of the state value.
        standardDeviation - is a statistical value to describe the standard deviation of the state value
        mean - is a statistical value to describe the mean of continuous state values.
        timeWeighting - is a statistical value to describe the duration of connection of the unit. 1 means max connection time in a specific period and 0 zero connection time.
